1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper discusses the use of the dataset for training and evaluation of deep learning-based methods, as well as benchmarking SLAM algorithms. This is a clear indication that the paper belongs to the computer vision sub-category. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper mentions the use of inertial measurements and trajectories, which are commonly used in robotics applications. 
3. cs.GR (Graphics): The paper discusses the rendering of high-resolution and high frame-rate video sequences, which is a key aspect of computer graphics. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Graphics): The paper leverages millions of professional interior designs and production-level furniture and object assets, which are commonly used in computer graphics applications. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper mentions the use of deep learning-based methods for training and evaluation, which falls under the machine learning sub-category.
